b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48462.htm)  [Next](sbe48464.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n16\\. And destruction.\n\nThere is moreover a Vedanta-text which declares the knowledge of Brahman to\ndestroy work-good and evil- which is the root of all the afflictions of\ntransmigratory existence: 'The knot of the heart is broken, all doubts are\nsolved, all his works perish when He has been beheld who is high and low' (Mu.\nUp. II, 2, 8). This also contradicts the view of knowledge being subordinate\nto works.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 17. And of him who is chaste...](sbe48464.htm)\n\n"